{"title":"[GSoC Daily Log]: Exar drivers","created_at":"2014-06-24 18:00:00 UTC","author":"Rohit (VGA Extension)","content":"<div dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left;\" trbidi=\"on\"><div dir=\"ltr\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-ea2c611e-d27c-dcf1-f5c7-d71301459df8\" style=\"line-height: 1.15; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-top: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: black; font-family: Arial; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\">Tuesday, 24th June 2014:</span></div><div dir=\"ltr\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-ea2c611e-d27c-dcf1-f5c7-d71301459df8\" style=\"line-height: 1.15; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-top: 0pt;\"><br /></div><ul style=\"margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-top: 0pt;\"><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"background-color: transparent; color: black; font-family: Arial; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; list-style-type: disc; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\"><div dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.15; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-top: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: black; font-family: Arial; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\">Tried Ajith’s UART code on linux. </span></div></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"background-color: transparent; color: black; font-family: Arial; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; list-style-type: disc; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\"><div dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.15; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-top: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: black; font-family: Arial; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\">Shenki’s updated driver also didn’t work for me</span></div></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"background-color: transparent; color: black; font-family: Arial; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; list-style-type: disc; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\"><div dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.15; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-top: 0pt;\"><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: black; font-family: Arial; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\">Atlast, since the Vizzini module was blocking my BeagleboneBlack’s USB-Serial from funtioning, I removed it and to my surprise also found the Exar one detected as CDC_ACM device at ttyACM1 and BBB at ttyACM0. Both are working fine</span></div></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"background-color: transparent; color: black; font-family: Arial; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; list-style-type: disc; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: black; font-family: Arial; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\">Searched for daisy chain enabled SPI EEPROM devices. Couldn’t find them. Updated the doc with additional details regarding this.</span></li></ul></div><div class=\"author\">\n  <span>\n    <i>Originally posted on <a href=\"http://dreamsxtrinsic.blogspot.com/\">Dreams eXtrinsic</a></i>\n  </span>\n</div>\n"}